  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Colombia: Building Trust, Relationships, and Community Coexistence, and Preventing Rural Violence with a Human Rights Approach</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project constitutes the third phase of a programme which has been implemented in PDET (Development Plans with a Territorial Focus) municipalities in Colombia since 2018. This third phase aims at contributing to the Government of Colombia&#x2019;s efforts to build trust, improve coexistence and reduce rural violence in the country. This is expected to be achieved through an increase of capacities of the National Police in implementing strategies to guarantee the prevention of violence in rural communities with a community and human rights approach. The project also intends to prioritize communities and strengthen their social infrastructure to prevent violence and promote peacebuilding, reconstruction of the social fabric, trust, security, inclusion, prevention of Gender-Based Violence, and community integration by developing community initiatives with their participation.</narrative>
  </description>
